page.description: Add several pairs, separated by '=', items separated by cr-lf.

argument.name: pairs
argument.description: A list of entries to add to a StringDictionary list. Each entry is composed of a pair of values in the format: Key_Value = Data_Value. Each pair of values is followed by a CR-LF.

page.discussion: The .INITIALIZE() method adds multiple entries to a StringDictionary list.
page.example: dim sd as StringDictionary dim values as C values = <<%a% One=a Two=b Three=c %a% dd.initialize(values)
